<p>I'm writing <code>ContainerRequestFilter</code> to inspect request headers and provide a pluggable authentication mechanism which would iterate the configured AS security realms (e.g. Glassfish) and provide a custom <code>SecurityContext</code>. I'm trying to inject the <code>RealmsManager</code> (defined in <code>com.sun.enterprise.security.auth.realm.RealmsManager</code>[1]), which is annotated as <code>@Singleton</code> in the <code>ContainerRequestFilter</code>. This is my code:</p>  <pre><code>public class AuthenticationFilter implements ContainerRequestFilter {      @Inject     RealmsManager rm;      @Override     public void filter(ContainerRequestContext requestContext) throws IOException {         if (rm != null) {             requestContext.abortWith(Response.ok("OKAY").build());          } else {             requestContext.abortWith(Response.ok("NULL").build());         } } </code></pre>  <p>but I get this error while deploying the WAR:</p>  <pre><code>org.jboss.weld.exceptions.DeploymentException: WELD-001408: Unsatisfied     dependencies for type RealmsManager with qualifiers @Default     at injection point [BackedAnnotatedField] @Inject </code></pre>  <p>How can I inject the <code>RelamsManager</code> singleton in a <code>ContainerRequestFilter</code>?</p>  <p>[1] Here's the source of <code>RealmsManager</code>: <a href="https://svn.java.net/svn/glassfish~svn/trunk/main/nucleus/security/core/src/main/java/com/sun/enterprise/security/auth/realm/RealmsManager.java" rel="nofollow">https://svn.java.net/svn/glassfish~svn/trunk/main/nucleus/security/core/src/main/java/com/sun/enterprise/security/auth/realm/RealmsManager.java</a></p>